description: Never read local secret files without explicit approval
alwaysApply: true
---

# Secret File Handling

- Never read `.env`, `.env.*`, `*.pem`, `*.key`, `credentials*.json`, or similar secret-bearing files.
- If debugging seems to require one of these files, stop and ask the user first.
- Prefer checking only variable names, schema, or example files like `.env.example`.
- Never print, quote, summarize, or paraphrase secret values from local files.
- If a secret is accidentally exposed, advise the user to rotate it and avoid re-reading the file.
